cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper presents a segmentation paradigm that uses a graph cut approach to separate an object from the background. The method is evaluated on 2D and 3D images, indicating a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a template shape suggests a potential focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and graphics (cs.GR). The application of the method to brain tumor datasets suggests a potential focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
